---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Baby Name Meaning Finder" 
  description="Find the perfect baby name with deep numerological meaning. Discover how Chaldean numerology reveals the hidden vibrations behind popular and unique baby names."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-20">
    
    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <span class="inline-block bg-zinc-800 text-purple-400 text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Baby Names</span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
        Baby Name Meaning Finder: How Numerology Shapes Your Child's Destiny
      </h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Choosing a baby name is one of the most profound decisions a parent can make. Beyond cultural heritage and aesthetics, every name carries a unique numerical vibration that can influence your child's personality, relationships, and life path. Discover how Chaldean name numerology can guide you to a name that resonates with your baby's cosmic blueprint.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Quick Finder Tool -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-900/30 to-cyan-900/20 border border-purple-500/20 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Quick Baby Name Number Finder</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
        <input 
          type="text" 
          id="babyNameInput"
          placeholder="Enter a baby name..."
          class="flex-1 bg-black border border-zinc-700 text-white rounded-lg px-4 py-3 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-purple-500 transition-all"
        />
        <button 
          id="babyNameBtn"
          class="bg-white text-black px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-zinc-200 transition-colors shrink-0"
        >
          Find Number
        </button>
      </div>
      <div id="babyResult" class="hidden mt-4 p-4 bg-zinc-900 rounded-xl flex items-start gap-4">
        <div id="babyNum" class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-400 to-cyan-400 shrink-0"></div>
        <div>
          <p id="babyTitle" class="text-white font-semibold"></p>
          <p id="babyDesc" class="text-zinc-400 text-sm mt-1"></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc max-w-none space-y-8 text-zinc-300">

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-zinc-800 pb-4">What Is Numerology for Baby Names?</h2>
      <p>Numerology is the ancient study of the mystical relationship between numbers and life events. When applied to baby names, it uses a system — most famously the <strong>Chaldean system</strong> — to assign a numerical value to each letter of the alphabet. The sum of these values, reduced to a single digit (or Master Number), reveals the name's core vibration.</p>
      <p>This number is known as the <strong>Expression Number</strong> or <strong>Destiny Number</strong>. It is believed to shape the core identity and natural talents that will define your child's path in life.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-zinc-800 pb-4">The Chaldean vs. Pythagorean System</h2>
      <p>Two major systems are used in name numerology. The <strong>Chaldean system</strong> is considered the older and more accurate of the two, originating from ancient Babylon. It assigns values from 1 to 8, with 9 being sacred and excluded from assignment. The <strong>Pythagorean (or Western) system</strong> is simpler, assigning values 1–9 sequentially to the alphabet.</p>
      <p>At Name Numerology Hub, we primarily use the <strong>Chaldean system</strong> for its historical depth and accuracy in readings.</p>
      
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 overflow-x-auto">
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-4 text-center">Chaldean Numerology Chart</h3>
        <table class="w-full text-center text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800 text-zinc-400">
              <th class="pb-2">Number</th>
              <th class="pb-2">Letters</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-zinc-300">
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50"><td class="py-2 text-purple-400 font-bold">1</td><td>A, I, J, Q, Y</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50"><td class="py-2 text-cyan-400 font-bold">2</td><td>B, K, R</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50"><td class="py-2 text-pink-400 font-bold">3</td><td>C, G, L, S</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50"><td class="py-2 text-yellow-400 font-bold">4</td><td>D, M, T</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50"><td class="py-2 text-green-400 font-bold">5</td><td>E, H, N, X</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50"><td class="py-2 text-orange-400 font-bold">6</td><td>U, V, W</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50"><td class="py-2 text-blue-400 font-bold">7</td><td>O, Z</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="py-2 text-red-400 font-bold">8</td><td>F, P</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-zinc-800 pb-4">Meaning of Each Name Number (1–9)</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        {[
          { num: 1, name: "The Pioneer", color: "purple", desc: "Leadership, independence, originality. A name with this vibration produces a natural-born leader." },
          { num: 2, name: "The Peacemaker", color: "cyan", desc: "Harmony, cooperation, sensitivity. This child will be empathetic and a great team player." },
          { num: 3, name: "The Creator", color: "pink", desc: "Creativity, self-expression, joy. Expect an artistic, social, and joyful child." },
          { num: 4, name: "The Builder", color: "yellow", desc: "Stability, discipline, hard work. This child will be grounded and reliable." },
          { num: 5, name: "The Explorer", color: "green", desc: "Freedom, adventure, change. A curious and adaptable child who loves new experiences." },
          { num: 6, name: "The Nurturer", color: "orange", desc: "Love, family, responsibility. A caring and compassionate child who loves to help." },
          { num: 7, name: "The Seeker", color: "blue", desc: "Wisdom, spirituality, analysis. A deep thinker who is drawn to knowledge and truth." },
          { num: 8, name: "The Achiever", color: "red", desc: "Ambition, power, abundance. A driven child destined for material and professional success." },
          { num: 9, name: "The Humanitarian", color: "indigo", desc: "Compassion, wisdom, service. An old soul dedicated to making the world a better place." },
        ].map(({ num, name, color, desc }) => (
          <div class={`bg-zinc-900/70 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-4`}>
            <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-zinc-200 mb-1">{num}</div>
            <div class={`text-sm font-semibold text-${color}-400 mb-2`}>{name}</div>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs leading-relaxed">{desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-zinc-800 pb-4">Tips for Choosing a Name with Good Vibration</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 list-none">
        {[
          "Calculate the name number for your top choices using our Name Hub tool.",
          "Consider the father's and mother's name numbers for compatibility.",
          "A Name Number that matches or complements the parents' Life Path numbers is considered auspicious.",
          "Avoid names that reduce to the same number as major challenges in the family's numerological chart.",
          "Test both formal name and common nickname — the one the child will actually use daily matters most."
        ].map(tip => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-zinc-300 text-sm">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-purple-400 shrink-0 mt-1.5"></span>
            {tip}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>

    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mt-16 bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Ready to Analyze a Name?</h3>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">Use our full Name Hub to get a complete report including personality traits and compatibility scores.</p>
      <a href="/name-analysis" class="inline-block bg-white text-black px-8 py-3 rounded-full font-semibold hover:bg-zinc-200 transition-colors">
        Go to Name Hub →
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>

  <script>
    const chaldean: Record<string, number> = {
      a:1,b:2,c:3,d:4,e:5,f:8,g:3,h:5,i:1,j:1,k:2,l:3,m:4,
      n:5,o:7,p:8,q:1,r:2,s:3,t:4,u:6,v:6,w:6,x:5,y:1,z:7
    };
    function reduce(n: number): number {
      while (n > 9 && n !== 11 && n !== 22 && n !== 33)
        n = String(n).split('').reduce((s, d) => s + parseInt(d), 0);
      return n;
    }
    const titles: Record<number, [string, string]> = {
      1: ["The Pioneer", "Leadership, independence, and originality define this name. A natural-born innovator."],
      2: ["The Peacemaker", "Harmony, cooperation, and sensitivity shine through this name."],
      3: ["The Creator", "Creativity, self-expression, and joyfulness are the hallmarks of this vibration."],
      4: ["The Builder", "Stability, discipline, and reliability are woven into this name."],
      5: ["The Explorer", "Freedom, curiosity, and adaptability are this name's gifts."],
      6: ["The Nurturer", "Love, compassion, and responsibility radiate from this name."],
      7: ["The Seeker", "Wisdom, spirituality, and analytical depth define this vibration."],
      8: ["The Achiever", "Ambition, power, and material success are embedded in this name."],
      9: ["The Humanitarian", "Compassion, wisdom, and a desire to serve humanity characterize this name."],
      11: ["The Visionary", "Extraordinary intuition and spiritual inspiration. (Master Number)"],
      22: ["The Architect", "The power to manifest grand visions into reality. (Master Number)"],
    };
    document.getElementById('babyNameBtn')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const val = (document.getElementById('babyNameInput') as HTMLInputElement).value.trim();
      if (!val) return;
      const sum = val.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g,'').split('').reduce((s,c) => s + (chaldean[c]||0), 0);
      const num = reduce(sum);
      const [title, desc] = titles[num] || ["Unique Vibration", "This name carries a rare and complex energy."];
      (document.getElementById('babyNum') as HTMLElement).textContent = num.toString();
      (document.getElementById('babyTitle') as HTMLElement).textContent = title;
      (document.getElementById('babyDesc') as HTMLElement).textContent = desc;
      (document.getElementById('babyResult') as HTMLElement).classList.remove('hidden');
    });
    document.getElementById('babyNameInput')?.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if ((e as KeyboardEvent).key === 'Enter') document.getElementById('babyNameBtn')?.click();
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
